des:
AWOL FM - Progressive house and old school dance from Northern Ireland

Detailed description -AWOL is a loose collective of (mostly) Northern Ireland based DJs and music lovers - playing old school dance from the 1980s to 2000s, and progressive house from any era. Established in 1994, AWOL first broadcast on BCR 96.7fm Belfast. Decks were set up in-studio, and Northern Ireland's top DJs of the era entertained the province's rave massive after club closing time on Saturday nights - the ultimate after-party!

Broadcasting from 6pm Friday until early Monday, then highlights from the weekend play on rotation during the week. Line-ups and other details can be found on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/groups/awolfm/ and on our website at awolfm.com. Highlights include...

The Friday Night Tune Jam - AWOL FM's live request show presented by AWOL founder Phil West.
Thump Saturday - banging it up every Saturday night.
Sequel Sunday - Phil Sloan and guests deliver world-class progressive house every Sunday morning.

Come on in, turn it up, and enjoy!
